The paper deals with the problem of multi-object tracking in autonomous vehicles, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The modifications proposed in the paper involve probabilistic modeling and machine learning, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the real-time implementation of the modified tracking framework, which is relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
